name: printed wiring board production, for surface mounting, Pb containing surface | printed wiring board, for surface mounting, Pb containing surface | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3120/documentation

This dataset represents the assembly of 1 m2 of a 6-layer FR-4 printed wiring board. It is based on  a 1.6 mm thick 6-layer PWB with a hot air solder leveling (HAL) surface finishing with a tin-lead-mixture (7.2 g Sn and 4.23 g Pb per m2 PWB), with soldermask, for surface mount applications, without mounted components with a square weight of 3.26 kg  used in ICT applications. Main data are taken from environmental reports of 3 German PWB producers, plus from literature.

From reception of raw materials at the factory gate.

This dataset includes (raw) materials, infrastructure, energy consumption, emissions to air and water and waste amounts. Not included into this dataset is the mounting of the PWB.
category: C:Manufacturing/26:Manufacture of computer, electronic and optical products/261:Manufacture of electronic components and boards/2610:Manufacture of electronic components and boards

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This module is based on information from European producers that are seen as representative for the global situation.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Average PWB production composed of: substrate preparation, imaging, exposure, etching, sandwiching, activation and accelaration steps as well as copper plating, cleaning, oxidification, dry vacuum lamination, micro etching, hot air levelling.

exchanges.description:
EcoSpold01Location=GLO
Typically, a printed wiring board (PWB) consists of a number of electric current conducting and non-conducting layers which are sandwiched together. Printed wiring boards are the interconnective electrical framework and physical structure that hold together the various electronic components.
